WEBVTT

00:28.362 --> 00:29.363
Is it bad?

00:30.531 --> 00:32.073
Is it bad?

00:32.156 --> 00:33.158
Nah.

00:42.709 --> 00:43.710
Stop the car.

00:49.466 --> 00:50.467
Stop the car!

00:53.220 --> 00:54.263
What are you doing?

00:54.847 --> 00:57.140
-Get away! Close the door!
-No! Let me go!

00:57.224 --> 00:59.351
-Get the door! Natalie! Hold on!
-Stop the car!

00:59.434 --> 01:02.020
-Get her back in.
-Close the fucking door!

01:04.690 --> 01:06.024
Get her back in.

01:08.402 --> 01:09.778
Now!

01:13.198 --> 01:15.576
-Please, we have to go back.
-Strap her in.

01:15.659 --> 01:19.454
Please. We have to turn around.
We can't leave her there. Stop the car!

01:19.538 --> 01:21.373
What are you doing? That was mad.

01:21.456 --> 01:23.792
You're okay, just breathe. Just breathe.

01:23.876 --> 01:25.627
-We're gonna get help now.
-Fuck's sake.

01:25.711 --> 01:26.879
Aren't we?

01:27.379 --> 01:28.714
I am help.

01:30.174 --> 01:31.216
Where are we going?

01:34.052 --> 01:35.971
You could drive a bit faster.

01:36.680 --> 01:39.016
I could if I wanted to attract attention.

01:39.099 --> 01:42.769
Yeah, but we need attention, don't we?
Someone tried to kill us. He's been shot.

01:42.853 --> 01:44.605
-People are dead.
-We need to call the police.

01:45.189 --> 01:47.107
You sure that wasn't
who we just left behind?

01:52.779 --> 01:53.989
There's no going back.

02:59.388 --> 03:01.223
Wait. What's happening?

03:16.071 --> 03:18.699
-Follow me.
-Where the fuck are we?

03:20.784 --> 03:22.035
Dude.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.923
Nice and quiet, all right?

03:52.774 --> 03:55.986
Geez. Sorry. Sorry.

04:12.002 --> 04:13.003
You okay?

04:13.962 --> 04:14.963
Yeah.

04:41.323 --> 04:42.324
Turn it off.

04:45.577 --> 04:48.789
Find some candles.
I'll check the rest of the place.

05:07.558 --> 05:08.559
Let's go.

05:09.059 --> 05:11.186
Now. Before he comes back.

05:19.862 --> 05:21.655
Shouldn't we wait to see
what he's got to say?

05:22.614 --> 05:24.032
You've been shot, Eddie.

05:24.116 --> 05:25.367
Yeah. I'm okay.

05:26.034 --> 05:28.078
But he's not. He's a psycho.

05:28.787 --> 05:30.539
This is the only way we get answers.

05:32.249 --> 05:34.251
Come on, give me the keys.

07:15.018 --> 07:17.479
Hey, do you think he knows
what this is all about?

07:19.481 --> 07:20.691
Was he dead?

07:23.318 --> 07:24.486
Who?

07:26.154 --> 07:27.781
The man I shot. Was he dead?

07:28.657 --> 07:30.325
I don't know. It was dark.

07:30.409 --> 07:31.910
That shot would've killed a zombie.

07:33.161 --> 07:34.371
Dude.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.874
But it was an accident, right? Soâ€¦

07:40.711 --> 07:45.841
Anyone find anything with a name
or password on? Bills, receipts, notes?

07:45.924 --> 07:47.009
What are you looking for?

07:47.092 --> 07:50.220
Can you please fill in a few gaps for us?
We're a tiny bit freaked out about--

07:50.304 --> 07:51.388
Everything.

07:51.471 --> 07:52.764
Everything. Thanks.

07:53.348 --> 07:55.392
-How did you find us?
-And why?

07:57.603 --> 07:58.979
Someone tried to kill me.

07:59.563 --> 08:02.608
It makes sense it was
whoever's trying to make it look like

08:02.691 --> 08:03.984
I kidnapped Leo Newman.

08:04.067 --> 08:05.569
You mean, you didn't kidnap him?

08:07.237 --> 08:08.989
I went to find out what she knows.

08:10.240 --> 08:13.076
Saw them get lifted, then I followed.

08:14.536 --> 08:15.621
Well, thank God you did.

08:15.704 --> 08:17.456
I don't think he did it
out of the kindness of his heart.

08:17.539 --> 08:19.499
I did it because you're my best chance

08:19.583 --> 08:23.504
of finding out what the fuck is going on
and why we've been lumped together.

08:23.587 --> 08:24.796
It's your fault.

08:28.050 --> 08:30.010
You're the one who's been texting me.

08:30.093 --> 08:33.179
You were on the motorbike.
This is all you.

08:33.263 --> 08:34.431
You two know each other?

08:34.515 --> 08:35.515
What motorbike?

08:36.265 --> 08:37.893
You shot me yesterday.

08:37.976 --> 08:40.437
I knew if you'd gone to the police
they'd put you in a vest.

08:41.605 --> 08:43.815
I didn't go to the police.

08:43.899 --> 08:47.528
If I'd wanted to kill you, you'd be dead.

08:51.073 --> 08:52.824
What the hell is going on here?

09:04.127 --> 09:05.379
Who are you?

09:05.462 --> 09:08.340
You know who he is.
The police told us. He's a trained killer.

09:08.423 --> 09:09.883
But I'm not your enemy.

09:09.967 --> 09:13.345
We're the only people that any of us
can trust even a little bit right now.

09:13.971 --> 09:16.807
And we have a couple of hours, tops,
to share what we know.

09:16.890 --> 09:19.643
Whoever sent those guys
already know it's gone bad.

09:19.726 --> 09:20.727
So, who were they?

09:20.811 --> 09:22.938
-Black ops, ex-military.
-How can you be sure?

09:23.021 --> 09:24.147
How do you think?

09:26.733 --> 09:29.194
-Sent by who?
-British authorities, FBI.

09:29.278 --> 09:31.196
Are you really saying
I shot a police officer?

09:31.280 --> 09:33.448
Well, you killed
our best chance of finding out.

09:36.201 --> 09:37.744
So, you think he's definitely dead?

09:41.164 --> 09:42.165
Seriously?

09:45.752 --> 09:48.463
The good news is that
officially it didn't happen.

09:48.547 --> 09:52.426
That scene will be clear by now.
Maybe apart from her sister's body.

09:52.509 --> 09:53.594
Natalie? Natalie!

09:54.803 --> 09:56.138
Natalie!

10:02.519 --> 10:06.148
-No. Get off. Get off me.
-Hey. Stop.

10:06.231 --> 10:07.608
No, I won't leave her there.

10:07.691 --> 10:09.985
They can't get away with this.
It did happen.

10:12.279 --> 10:13.739
Stop.

10:21.455 --> 10:22.873
Anybody else got a phone?

10:23.999 --> 10:25.709
No, they've already taken them off us.

10:27.461 --> 10:31.048
Listen, we're all in this togeth--

10:32.216 --> 10:34.426
She's gone. Do you hear? Gone.

10:40.015 --> 10:42.935
Now, do you want to find out
who did it or not?

10:52.110 --> 10:54.196
So, why us?

10:54.279 --> 10:56.740
Don't get too comfortable.
We haven't got long.

10:56.823 --> 10:59.368
Come on. What do we have in common?

11:03.497 --> 11:05.415
We're all British
and we were all in New York

11:05.499 --> 11:06.959
on the day Leo Newman was kidnapped.

11:08.585 --> 11:09.670
Why were you there?

11:10.671 --> 11:11.797
We've been through this.

11:12.381 --> 11:13.757
For the police, I know.

11:13.841 --> 11:17.010
But this time you can tell the truth.
We all can.

11:18.720 --> 11:21.139
What's said here goes no further.
Are we agreed?

11:29.189 --> 11:31.400
I spoke
at a Cooper Newman Foundation event.

11:31.483 --> 11:32.693
I didn't want to, but I--

11:32.776 --> 11:34.152
Why not?

11:35.654 --> 11:38.490
Four years ago, I questioned
whether Leo Newman should be offered

11:38.574 --> 11:39.616
a place at the university

11:39.700 --> 11:42.244
and the ethics of taking money
from his mother's company.

11:42.953 --> 11:44.538
There was a full investigation.

11:44.621 --> 11:46.748
Everything was found to be aboveboard,
and that was it.

11:47.624 --> 11:48.917
Did you talk to him while he was there?

11:50.252 --> 11:51.753
-No.
-Really?

11:52.421 --> 11:56.008
Yes, really. And this does feel
quite like the police interview, actually.

11:56.091 --> 11:57.634
But you must know him?

11:59.803 --> 12:00.804
Why must I?

12:01.889 --> 12:04.016
Because they're saying
he's a student at Oxford.

12:04.725 --> 12:09.813
Have you ever been to a university?
No, of course. Well, they're big places.

12:09.897 --> 12:11.106
Yeah, with lots of windows. I know.

12:11.190 --> 12:13.859
Uh-huh, and there are
more than 20,000 students at Oxford,

12:13.942 --> 12:14.943
and I'm one of them.

12:15.027 --> 12:17.613
No, more to the point, I'm no one.
That's why this is so mad.

12:17.696 --> 12:19.323
He's a carpet salesman.

12:19.406 --> 12:20.532
No, I'm not.

12:21.241 --> 12:22.576
Quite a coincidence though.

12:22.659 --> 12:24.244
Do we look like kidnappers to you?

12:24.328 --> 12:25.704
What does a kidnapper look like?

12:25.787 --> 12:26.788
You.

12:31.001 --> 12:33.629
You looked more like Lara Croft
than a professor back there.

12:33.712 --> 12:34.796
I'm not a professor.

12:34.880 --> 12:36.256
And I'm not a carpet salesman.

12:36.340 --> 12:37.508
So what are you then?

12:38.175 --> 12:39.718
Yeah, why were you in New York?

12:39.801 --> 12:43.263
I went to meet Cooper Newman PR
about a job. Cybersecurity.

12:43.347 --> 12:46.558
I've got a business.
I'm starting it, soon.

12:46.642 --> 12:47.809
Wait--

12:47.893 --> 12:51.104
A multinational corporation
turning over a billion dollars a year

12:51.188 --> 12:52.397
needs to upgrade security,

12:52.481 --> 12:55.901
so they call
for a West London carpet salesman?

12:55.984 --> 12:58.529
-I'm not a--
-Telling the truth, are you?

12:59.821 --> 13:01.907
Do you all understand how deep you're in?

13:02.741 --> 13:04.618
This isn't just about the Newman kid now.

13:04.701 --> 13:06.370
Who do you think
they'll blame her sister on?

13:09.414 --> 13:11.458
-No.
-Fuck, yeah.

13:11.542 --> 13:13.377
Sorry, why should we believe you?

13:15.003 --> 13:17.548
Tell us what you know.
It's your face all over the news.

13:17.631 --> 13:22.302
And whereas your face
isn't anywhere, student. Why's that?

13:22.386 --> 13:25.556
'Cause I was arrested later,
and I wasn't staying in the hotel.

13:25.639 --> 13:29.643
And my face is all over
the front of every fucking newspaper.

13:29.726 --> 13:30.727
Pixilated.

13:31.478 --> 13:34.606
I don't know. Maybe I did see Leo at uni.

13:34.690 --> 13:36.942
Might've spoken to him. I speak to anyone.

13:38.068 --> 13:39.111
Police might have found out

13:39.194 --> 13:41.280
that we were at the same lecture
or at the same pub once,

13:41.363 --> 13:44.283
and then I happened to be in New York
on the day he's kidnapped.

13:44.366 --> 13:47.536
And suddenly, I'm Baby Driver.

13:47.619 --> 13:48.871
Where you from?

13:48.954 --> 13:50.163
Wales, originally.

13:52.165 --> 13:54.168
-Which part?
-Cardiff.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.338
Your parents married there?

13:58.422 --> 13:59.631
-What?
-Answer.

13:59.715 --> 14:03.260
Enough. Your turn.
Your turn to answer to us. To me.

14:03.343 --> 14:04.928
You've been blackmailing me for two years.

14:05.929 --> 14:07.264
Not me, Natalie.

14:08.056 --> 14:12.186
I know you're angry,
but I was just the collector.

14:12.269 --> 14:14.813
The way I heard it, you stole that money
in the first place. Soâ€¦

14:14.897 --> 14:16.899
Yes, and I paid it back.

14:16.982 --> 14:19.776
But those last two cash drops were
for you, weren't they?

14:19.860 --> 14:22.529
That's the reason
I was in New York, isn't it?

14:22.613 --> 14:23.947
Why didn't you pick up?

14:24.031 --> 14:26.074
Who first contacted you
about the New York drop?

14:26.158 --> 14:28.619
You did. Tell the truth.

14:29.536 --> 14:32.664
The police said that
the company I defrauded are owned by CNPR.

14:32.748 --> 14:35.501
Did you know that? Did they send you?

14:36.168 --> 14:37.794
Honestly, I don't know.

14:39.213 --> 14:42.424
It's in nobody's interest for me to have
too much information, you know?

14:54.937 --> 14:56.396
Who do you work for?

14:56.480 --> 14:58.815
I don't work for anybody,
as discussed. I'm a student.

14:58.899 --> 15:00.359
-Studying what?
-History.

15:00.442 --> 15:01.527
All of it?

15:01.610 --> 15:03.737
-What?
-Which period? Answer.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.906
-Ancient. What is this?
-Ancient British or what?

15:05.989 --> 15:07.157
Oh, fuck you.

15:07.241 --> 15:08.283
Eddie!

15:08.367 --> 15:09.868
Eddie, are you all right?

15:11.245 --> 15:13.539
Hey. Hey, you okay, mate?

15:14.706 --> 15:16.542
Someone find him a clean shirt.

15:30.973 --> 15:33.934
You can see the road from upstairs.
Will you keep an eye out?

15:37.646 --> 15:39.273
Go watch the front of the house.

15:41.066 --> 15:42.484
I'll deal with him.

17:08.862 --> 17:10.030
Oh, shit.

17:14.117 --> 17:17.119
Uh-oh. You're lucky, student.

17:18.704 --> 17:21.583
You're gonna have a proper scar
from this, if you live.

17:25.045 --> 17:26.046
Joke.

17:28.048 --> 17:31.176
Come on, come on. Oh, fuck.

17:43.021 --> 17:44.314
How is he?

17:45.315 --> 17:46.859
Bullet only winged him.

17:46.942 --> 17:49.278
-Didn't hurt anything vital.
-How can you tell?

17:49.361 --> 17:50.612
Fact he's breathing.

17:50.696 --> 17:51.697
Here.

17:52.406 --> 17:53.782
Take that out. Cut a square.

17:59.872 --> 18:01.540
Did you learn all this in the army?

18:07.337 --> 18:09.173
Is that where you first killed someone?

18:11.717 --> 18:13.010
Give me that.

18:14.553 --> 18:15.888
How'd it feel?

18:16.930 --> 18:18.182
The first time.

18:23.562 --> 18:25.689
That might be
the first time you've hit a human,

18:25.772 --> 18:27.691
but it's not the first time
you fired a gun.

18:28.901 --> 18:32.154
Well, you don't grow up on a farm
without knowing how to handle a rifle.

18:32.237 --> 18:33.530
Rifle's not a handgun.

18:34.531 --> 18:36.366
My grandfather collected handguns.

18:38.452 --> 18:39.453
One more.

18:47.252 --> 18:49.046
Right. Help me sit him up.

18:50.464 --> 18:51.548
Okay. Okay.

18:54.259 --> 18:55.594
Okay.

18:55.677 --> 18:56.803
Well, don't worry, it gets easier.

18:59.223 --> 19:00.349
You mean to live with?

19:00.432 --> 19:02.309
No, I mean killing people.

19:02.976 --> 19:04.478
The more you do it, the easier it gets.

19:07.064 --> 19:10.275
Here, drink this.
It's got salt and sugar in it.

19:12.611 --> 19:13.612
Fuck.

19:19.451 --> 19:20.577
Come on.

19:31.463 --> 19:32.506
Shit!

20:14.298 --> 20:16.884
-Good looking out.
-Sam?

20:17.885 --> 20:19.094
Is that you?

20:21.930 --> 20:23.348
I can't see the car.

20:30.105 --> 20:31.940
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

20:32.024 --> 20:35.360
There's no need for that, all right?
Just-- Let's be quiet and he'll leave.

20:35.444 --> 20:37.654
I thought you were away for a while.

20:58.509 --> 21:00.052
Take your shirt off.

21:00.135 --> 21:01.136
Sam?

21:01.845 --> 21:03.096
Are you home?

21:05.933 --> 21:06.934
Are you there?

21:08.894 --> 21:09.895
Sam?

21:13.065 --> 21:14.066
Geez.

21:15.526 --> 21:16.693
Who are you?

21:16.777 --> 21:20.822
Who are you?
And why are you pointing a gun at me?

21:20.906 --> 21:23.575
Well, I live next door. And I saw a light.

21:23.659 --> 21:25.077
Shit.

21:31.124 --> 21:33.210
Sorry, are you--

21:33.293 --> 21:34.753
David.

21:34.837 --> 21:37.673
David. Right. Okay. I think--

21:38.507 --> 21:40.259
Yeah, I think Uncle Sammy
told me about you.

21:40.342 --> 21:43.303
-Uncle?
-It's a term of endearment.

21:43.387 --> 21:45.097
We met while I was traveling.

21:46.557 --> 21:49.309
Are you the NGO friend of his daughter's?

21:49.393 --> 21:50.978
Married to the journalist?

21:51.061 --> 21:54.606
I've been away a while.
Is everyone armed here now?

21:54.690 --> 21:55.691
Sorry about that.

21:55.774 --> 21:58.402
No, I'm sorry for waking you.

22:02.990 --> 22:04.032
Is your husband with you?

22:06.702 --> 22:10.664
Did you not meet him?
When he was last over?

22:11.415 --> 22:12.416
No.

22:14.042 --> 22:15.627
I thought Sammy said thatâ€¦

22:17.254 --> 22:18.463
Baby?

22:29.183 --> 22:30.184
Yep?

22:31.018 --> 22:33.812
Sweetheart, this is David from next door.

22:33.896 --> 22:34.897
Hi, David.

22:36.148 --> 22:38.525
Good job on the neighborhood watch front.

22:38.609 --> 22:41.236
You must be Harry? A pleasure.

22:42.154 --> 22:45.240
Maybe we did meet.
You look familiar now I see you close up.

22:45.324 --> 22:47.159
I'd remember.

22:48.452 --> 22:49.912
I've read your book, you know.

22:50.621 --> 22:53.790
Did you? Well, I hope you bought it
rather than borrowed it.

22:53.874 --> 22:55.417
What did you think?

22:55.501 --> 22:57.044
Well, I was crying, of course.

22:57.127 --> 22:58.587
Me too. So sad.

22:58.670 --> 23:00.255
With laughter.

23:01.465 --> 23:03.717
-I mean, talk about light and shade.
-She's lying.

23:06.261 --> 23:07.596
She never reads my work.

23:08.222 --> 23:10.891
She thinks I don't know,
but the truth is I don't mind.

23:11.725 --> 23:14.019
I love her for other reasons.

23:14.102 --> 23:18.106
Well, I must--
Should be letting you two get someâ€¦

23:19.775 --> 23:21.151
You've got something on yourâ€¦

23:22.069 --> 23:23.403
Thanks.

23:24.905 --> 23:26.990
How long will you be staying for?

23:28.325 --> 23:30.369
We're gonna play it by ear.

23:31.537 --> 23:32.538
Right.

23:35.707 --> 23:36.917
Come on, Delta.

23:38.085 --> 23:39.419
Thanks, then. Bye.

23:41.588 --> 23:43.674
-You're an excellent liar.
-So are you.

23:43.757 --> 23:45.467
He knows that's blood. He'll be back.

23:46.385 --> 23:47.594
Sorry, guys.

23:49.096 --> 23:51.056
Hey, Eddie. How are you feeling?

23:52.224 --> 23:53.684
Yeah. Better.

24:02.734 --> 24:04.027
Where's my gun?

24:05.571 --> 24:06.613
Where's Natalie?

24:12.160 --> 24:13.161
Natalie?

24:13.996 --> 24:15.289
Natalie, what are you doing?

24:15.372 --> 24:16.957
Stop. Natalie, answer me.

24:17.040 --> 24:18.375
Leave me alone.

24:19.042 --> 24:20.043
Okay.

24:23.172 --> 24:24.173
Natalieâ€¦

24:24.840 --> 24:27.134
Natalie, please. You don't wanna do this.

24:28.886 --> 24:31.638
You don't know me.
You don't know anything about me.

24:32.931 --> 24:34.016
Yes. You're right.

24:34.099 --> 24:37.269
We're strangers. But for some reason,
we're all in the same mess.

24:38.979 --> 24:41.648
How many family members
did you lose tonight?

24:42.941 --> 24:44.693
I have lost people.

24:45.319 --> 24:47.529
And I know how it feels

24:47.613 --> 24:50.324
to blame yourself
for things that aren't your fault.

24:53.118 --> 24:57.539
It is my fault.
I'm the reason she was there.

25:01.084 --> 25:05.297
Mum has already buried
the only man she ever loved,

25:05.380 --> 25:12.012
and Mon-- Monique, she was--
She was the one. She madeâ€¦

25:14.223 --> 25:17.935
She made everything worthwhile for Mum
and for me andâ€¦

25:20.687 --> 25:22.272
She was gonna save the world.

25:23.357 --> 25:24.483
Natalie?

25:25.442 --> 25:29.446
I've got a daughter. She's called Daisy.

25:30.572 --> 25:33.909
And I love her more than I ever thought
I could ever love anything,

25:33.992 --> 25:36.662
and I am telling you, the only thing worse

25:36.745 --> 25:39.039
than your mum finding out
she lost one of her girls

25:39.122 --> 25:41.750
would be finding out she lost both.

25:44.586 --> 25:45.921
She'll never forgive me.

25:48.173 --> 25:50.092
And I'll never forgive myself.

25:51.093 --> 25:52.219
No!

26:00.185 --> 26:01.186
It's okay.

26:01.270 --> 26:02.479
Give that to me.

26:02.563 --> 26:04.565
You didn't kill her. They did.

26:04.648 --> 26:05.899
He's right.

26:05.983 --> 26:07.693
You need to take the safety off.

26:09.111 --> 26:12.030
We've all told lies, okay?

26:12.114 --> 26:13.615
We'll get to the truth.

26:21.331 --> 26:22.708
What did you lie about?

26:37.556 --> 26:41.810
