31:05.157 --> 31:06.366
Play the latest video.

31:08.076 --> 31:12.998
Okay, listen up. We all appreciate you
keeping this going for Leo's sake,

31:13.081 --> 31:16.043
but Miss Newman will not be making
any statement

31:16.126 --> 31:18.587
-about tonight's communications.
-What is he talking about?

31:18.670 --> 31:21.673
We'll be talking to you
as soon as we have something to say.

31:21.757 --> 31:22.799
What's the connection

31:22.883 --> 31:25.552
between Katherine and the man
in the picture, Eric Cresswell?

31:25.636 --> 31:27.930
We know as much as you do right now, Jill.

31:29.890 --> 31:32.267
-I have nothing more to say. Sorry.
-What "man in the picture"?

31:33.143 --> 31:34.353
Who's Eric Cresswell?

31:35.395 --> 31:37.397
How do you know about the secret server?

31:38.398 --> 31:40.734
-Can somebody tell me what's going on?
-What was that?

31:41.485 --> 31:44.696
-What did you see?
-I don't know. Some movement, I think.

31:45.989 --> 31:47.032
Where?

31:47.115 --> 31:48.951
Over there, between those trees.

31:49.743 --> 31:50.744
Show me.

31:54.498 --> 31:56.333
Just here. Justâ€¦

31:56.875 --> 31:57.876
Hey, hey.

32:16.186 --> 32:17.437
What are they doing?

32:19.565 --> 32:22.192
-Do you think it's the neighbor?
-Or the police.

32:52.764 --> 32:53.765
Yeah.

33:03.775 --> 33:04.985
Who were you phoning?

33:08.197 --> 33:09.198
Fuck you.

33:17.623 --> 33:20.375
Come on. Deep breaths.

33:21.335 --> 33:22.711
Should we go out?

33:22.794 --> 33:23.795
And do what?

33:24.713 --> 33:26.131
And what if they need help?

33:26.215 --> 33:28.342
Sean doesn't seem like the kind of person
who needs your help.

33:28.425 --> 33:30.969
-Thanks. But what about--
-Aadesh is with Sean.

33:36.391 --> 33:40.103
-Did that video say the kidnappers--
-Do you ever stop talking?

33:40.187 --> 33:42.689
I'm sorry to be a pain.
I have been kidnapped and shot tonight.

33:42.773 --> 33:45.901
-So, I am just a little bit fucking tense.
-Which college are you at?

33:47.569 --> 33:48.987
At Oxford, which college?

33:50.197 --> 33:51.490
Wolvesey.

33:52.032 --> 33:54.826
Right. So, you know Professor Cottler?

33:56.578 --> 33:57.704
No.

33:57.788 --> 33:59.164
What the fuck?

34:21.270 --> 34:22.271
What the fuck.

34:22.353 --> 34:24.565
What happened? Jesus.

34:24.648 --> 34:25.732
What's going on?

34:27.234 --> 34:28.235
You all right?

34:31.280 --> 34:32.781
Sean.

34:32.864 --> 34:33.949
Go on.

34:37.077 --> 34:39.788
I found a phone.
I was trying to make a call.

34:39.871 --> 34:41.873
-Who to?
-The police.

34:41.956 --> 34:43.417
-So he says.
-No, it's true.

34:43.500 --> 34:46.085
I was trying to phone that Vanessa woman.

34:46.170 --> 34:50.174
-I really think we can trust her.
-I've told you you can't trust anyone.

34:50.257 --> 34:51.675
Yeah, including you.

34:51.757 --> 34:54.052
Yeah, including you. Exactly.

34:54.136 --> 34:55.804
He says it's not safe to call the police,

34:55.888 --> 34:57.514
but what if it's only him
it's not safe for?

34:57.598 --> 34:58.807
We haven't killed anyone.

35:04.271 --> 35:06.440
You can check if he's telling the truth
from his call history.

35:06.523 --> 35:08.942
Yeah, but I didn't actually
get to dial before he destroyed it.

35:09.026 --> 35:11.778
Swear down, it's true. I just--
I want this to be over, you guys.

35:13.197 --> 35:14.239
I don't buy it.

35:14.323 --> 35:16.742
The Forrest Gump act, yeah.

35:16.825 --> 35:19.620
We know he's smarter
than he looks. He fucking has to be.

35:20.120 --> 35:21.121
I agree.

35:22.080 --> 35:24.791
He ran out as soon as you asked him
about Martin Copeland.

35:25.334 --> 35:27.336
And if you're involved in this,

35:27.419 --> 35:30.005
that means you're part of the reason
Monique's dead,

35:30.088 --> 35:31.507
and you deserve to die

35:31.590 --> 35:34.676
in the middle of nowhere
just like she did.

35:34.760 --> 35:36.178
I'm warming to you.

35:36.261 --> 35:39.431
Okay, Natalie. Okay, okay.

35:45.103 --> 35:46.104
I'll tell you.

35:46.188 --> 35:47.648
Tell us what?

35:51.693 --> 35:52.986
Martin Copelandâ€¦

35:55.072 --> 35:59.284
came to my meeting in New York in person.

36:01.870 --> 36:03.956
-I couldn't believe it.
-Neither can I.

36:04.039 --> 36:06.583
Yeah, but, you see, the thing is
that what I did, right--

36:06.667 --> 36:10.796
One of the strategies I use
to sell my services is basicallyâ€¦

36:12.297 --> 36:13.298
I hacked them.

36:15.592 --> 36:18.220
Yeah, man. I hacked Cooper Newman.

36:18.303 --> 36:21.598
And then I told them what I'd done.
You see, I say,

36:21.682 --> 36:24.434
"Imagine if I wasn't a good guy,
right, who'd done this.

36:24.518 --> 36:28.230
Imagine if it was a baddie.
The damage I could do to your company.

36:28.313 --> 36:32.693
So employ me, and I'll stop the baddies
because only I know all their tricks."

36:32.776 --> 36:35.112
I take it you didn't tell
your friend Vanessa that part.

36:37.114 --> 36:38.532
I didn't tell my wife that part.

36:39.867 --> 36:42.703
He still wouldn't have met you. What else?

36:42.786 --> 36:44.496
What do you mean what else?
There's nothing else.

36:44.580 --> 36:46.164
-I don't believe you.
-Me neither.

36:46.248 --> 36:47.541
No. It's true, guys, I swear.

36:47.624 --> 36:51.211
I can't tell you why he was there,
but he was and that's it.

36:51.295 --> 36:52.796
That's all I know. All right?

36:54.298 --> 36:56.300
-What did you see?
-What do you mean? Where?

36:56.383 --> 36:58.969
You hacked their systems,
found a secret server,

36:59.052 --> 37:01.013
and presumably had a good look around.
What did you see?

37:01.096 --> 37:02.764
All sorts. I can't remember.
That wasn't the point.

37:02.848 --> 37:05.225
-Did you copy anything?
-What? I wasn't trying to blackmail them.

37:05.309 --> 37:08.228
-Although, technicallyâ€¦
-Think, think. We're running out of time.

37:08.312 --> 37:11.231
I don't know. All sorts of strategy stuff.

37:11.315 --> 37:13.400
Client briefs, financial reports.
Mostly boring.

37:13.483 --> 37:14.902
The only interesting things were emails.

37:14.985 --> 37:17.196
-You read people's private emails?
-No. Yeah.

37:17.279 --> 37:19.072
-Copeland's?
-Copeland's, yeah. Katherine Newman's.

37:19.156 --> 37:21.033
I knew about the ambassador thing
before it happened.

37:21.116 --> 37:22.284
Was the son mentioned?

37:22.367 --> 37:23.994
Yeah. They were making
succession plans about--

37:24.077 --> 37:25.913
-Who's doing that?
-Copeland.

37:25.996 --> 37:29.082
There was stuff about it being a new day.
A fresh start. Blah, blah, blah.

37:29.166 --> 37:31.835
-Who were those emails to?
-I don't fucking know!

37:32.503 --> 37:35.130
All right? I don't fucking know!

37:36.256 --> 37:38.675
Okay. What do we know?

37:39.885 --> 37:41.512
At the event I spoke at,

37:42.095 --> 37:46.391
Leo Newman was given formal responsibility
for running the Cooper Newman Foundation.

37:46.475 --> 37:50.687
Yeah. The shell company had me moving
a lot of money the past few months.

37:50.771 --> 37:53.023
Well, even if Copeland's nose was
put out of joint,

37:53.106 --> 37:54.525
how does kidnapping Leo help him?

38:01.448 --> 38:02.908
Anybody got any ideas?

38:10.332 --> 38:11.333
Where are you going?

38:14.294 --> 38:16.088
Sean, where are you going?

38:16.171 --> 38:17.798
It will be light soon. I need to change.

38:17.881 --> 38:20.425
Then I've got a few questions
for the organ-grinder.

38:20.509 --> 38:21.969
You're going to speak to Copeland?

38:22.052 --> 38:24.888
He's the link, isn't he?
He's what we've all got in common.

38:24.972 --> 38:28.141
Except you, student.
What's your connection to Copeland?

38:28.225 --> 38:30.227
I haven't got one as far as I know.

38:30.310 --> 38:34.106
What about your dad?
His business, it's in America, isn't it?

38:34.189 --> 38:35.774
America's massive.

38:35.858 --> 38:37.150
What exactly are you gonna do?

38:37.234 --> 38:40.153
My livelihood's gone.
One way or another, someone has to pay.

38:40.237 --> 38:42.364
But, what--
Are you actually going to New York?

38:42.906 --> 38:46.577
Wait, if Martin Copeland did this
to my family, to me,

38:46.660 --> 38:49.079
then I wanna know why, same as you.

38:50.289 --> 38:51.623
-I'm coming with you.
-No way.

38:52.291 --> 38:53.292
You owe me.

38:53.375 --> 38:56.253
Actually, I'd say we're even.

38:56.336 --> 38:59.882
And given the fact that I'm armed,
I'd quit while you're ahead.

38:59.965 --> 39:01.216
I can help you.

39:02.259 --> 39:03.468
There's more money.

39:05.095 --> 39:07.181
You wouldn't have hung around
if you had cash.

39:07.264 --> 39:08.891
How are you gonna get to America?

39:14.021 --> 39:15.731
NCA will have frozen
everything you've got.

39:16.481 --> 39:17.649
When they released us,

39:17.733 --> 39:21.111
I went to work and moved what was left
of the client account balance offshore.

39:21.195 --> 39:23.197
-They won't trace it in time.
-Why?

39:23.280 --> 39:24.281
What?

39:25.324 --> 39:26.491
Why did you do that?

39:27.576 --> 39:30.704
Because I thought I might still be able
to marry the man I love.

39:35.459 --> 39:37.920
-Hundred K.
-Natalie, what are you doing?

39:42.424 --> 39:44.635
Maybe I'll just torture you
till you transfer the money.

39:45.219 --> 39:46.720
Do I look like I care about dying?

39:54.937 --> 39:56.522
Change fast.

39:56.605 --> 39:59.024
There'll be a shirt or something
that fits you.

39:59.107 --> 40:00.943
Find a hat or glasses. Do your hair.

40:01.026 --> 40:02.861
Anything that alters
the shape of your head.

40:05.614 --> 40:09.201
Confuses facial recognition software.
So he's done this before.

40:09.993 --> 40:11.078
What about you?

40:52.119 --> 40:54.788
The latest communication
from the kidnappers

40:54.872 --> 40:55.998
came yesterday evening.

40:56.081 --> 40:58.792
And in the hours since,
investigators have been desperately trying

40:58.876 --> 41:02.337
to track the man identified
in the kidnapper's latest video

41:02.421 --> 41:04.131
as Eric Cresswell.

41:04.214 --> 41:05.465
A disgraced British scientist,

41:05.549 --> 41:07.634
Cresswell was forced
to resign from his post

41:07.718 --> 41:10.721
at Cambrook University
after an investigation,

41:10.804 --> 41:13.223
but no further details were made available
at the time.

41:13.307 --> 41:17.144
And the university has so far declined
to comment about their former employee.

41:18.228 --> 41:21.815
His connection to Katherine Newman
and what precisely the truth is

41:21.899 --> 41:23.358
remains a mystery.

41:23.442 --> 41:25.652
-Who's he?
-I don't know.

41:27.154 --> 41:29.448
Was there anything aboutâ€¦

41:30.532 --> 41:31.533
No.

41:38.248 --> 41:40.375
Can you help with this?

41:41.251 --> 41:42.252
Yeah.

41:47.299 --> 41:48.967
You sure you know what you're doing?

41:50.135 --> 41:51.136
No.

41:51.762 --> 41:53.388
But I have to do something.

42:00.437 --> 42:02.981
He's dangerous.
You know that better than anyone.

42:03.065 --> 42:04.483
There has to be another way.

42:05.067 --> 42:06.860
Well, I'm all ears

42:06.944 --> 42:10.405
'cause right now, I don't feel like
I've got any other option.

42:13.534 --> 42:14.535
What about you?

42:16.787 --> 42:18.247
I mean, do you know what you're doing?

42:20.374 --> 42:22.751
Like you say, he's dangerous.

42:22.835 --> 42:25.045
Do you really think
he's gonna let you walk out of here

42:25.128 --> 42:26.755
knowing where he's going and why?

42:28.423 --> 42:30.676
-He--
-He only shot me in the chest

42:30.759 --> 42:32.886
because he thought
I might still be useful. He's ruthless.

42:32.970 --> 42:34.596
So how can you trust him?

42:35.806 --> 42:37.516
Who said anything about trust?

42:39.226 --> 42:41.228
Can't go back,
and he's the only way forward.

42:42.479 --> 42:44.898
-What about your mum?
-She's strong.

42:46.316 --> 42:47.484
She's had to be.

42:50.445 --> 42:51.655
It's different for you.

42:52.739 --> 42:53.949
You've got a kid.

42:54.491 --> 42:55.576
As things stand,

42:55.659 --> 42:57.870
I'll lose any chance I had of
getting her back.

42:58.954 --> 43:00.330
I'll lose everything.

43:33.113 --> 43:34.114
Well, frankly,

43:34.198 --> 43:37.492
a scenario in which those responsible
ask for anything other than hard cash,

43:37.576 --> 43:41.538
unless it's politically motivated,
is already highly unusual.

43:41.622 --> 43:44.666
Do you believe then
that Newman's kidnap could be political?

43:44.750 --> 43:48.670
Perhaps even terrorist-related?
There has been speculation--

43:48.754 --> 43:50.506
I think if that's what we're seeing here,

43:50.589 --> 43:52.841
then it's potentially
a new strain of terrorism.

43:53.467 --> 43:55.928
Let's call it ethical terrorism.

43:56.011 --> 43:57.513
Ethical terrorism?

43:59.723 --> 44:00.933
Sounds pretty cool.

44:01.016 --> 44:03.852
"Cool"? My parents are gonna kill me.

44:03.936 --> 44:06.396
I haven't spoken to mine.
God knows what they're thinking.

44:07.189 --> 44:08.565
They might not be that surprised.

44:08.649 --> 44:09.816
They always expected their son

44:09.900 --> 44:13.529
to be hunted down by at least two
international law enforcement agencies?

44:13.612 --> 44:18.825
It is the latest in a long line
of fuckups, headaches, letdowns. For them.

44:21.620 --> 44:22.829
For Sonia.

44:31.797 --> 44:33.173
At least we're consistent.

44:35.384 --> 44:39.596
So, what do we do now, partner?

44:40.222 --> 44:42.432
Surely we can trust that Vanessa.

44:42.516 --> 44:45.644
Yeah, maybe, but even if she believes us,
what about Sonia and her family?

44:46.270 --> 44:49.106
And my parents, the university?
Are they going to take our word for it?

44:50.274 --> 44:54.778
-But if no one can prove that we did it--
-That's different to proving we didn't.

44:54.862 --> 44:56.405
How do you prove a negative?

45:01.535 --> 45:02.536
It's confusing.

45:02.619 --> 45:05.122
Not only for the authorities,
but also for the public.

45:05.205 --> 45:09.835
We're talking about a crime here,
and yet popular support is split

45:09.918 --> 45:13.839
between sympathy for a mother
who's missing her son

45:13.922 --> 45:16.550
and these faces of a growing movement

45:16.633 --> 45:22.472
that is sick and tired of being lied to
again and again by public figures.

45:25.684 --> 45:27.311
-That's us fucked, then.
-Exactly.

45:27.394 --> 45:31.273
Without any proof of our innocence,
the damage is already done, isn't it?

45:31.356 --> 45:33.192
Assuming he lets us leave here.

45:33.817 --> 45:35.569
What, you don't think he's planning to--

45:35.652 --> 45:40.407
Yeah. No. I don't know,
but I do think he's right.

45:40.490 --> 45:41.617
We can't trust anyone.

45:41.700 --> 45:44.912
And even if that goes for the five of us,
at least we know the rules.

45:48.040 --> 45:50.459
Wait, are you suggesting
that we should all go to--

45:50.542 --> 45:51.793
Got to bloody America.

45:51.877 --> 45:53.837
I can't quite believe it either, but yes.

45:55.464 --> 45:59.551
Unless any of you have any better ideas.
But just to remind you, you came to me.

45:59.635 --> 46:06.433
One second. Tara, you're saying
the five most wanted people in the UK

46:07.142 --> 46:11.063
should try to cross one of
the most secure borders in the world

46:11.146 --> 46:17.444
to return to the scene of the crime
they're accused of, in order to confront

46:17.528 --> 46:21.406
the crazy, powerful man
they think might have framed them

46:21.490 --> 46:25.911
for reasons no one seems to be able
to even guess at.

46:26.495 --> 46:27.579
And you're a professor?

46:27.663 --> 46:30.249
I'm not a fucking professor.
I'm a junior research fellow.

46:30.332 --> 46:32.876
I was-- Whatever.

46:32.960 --> 46:34.920
What about your daughter?

46:37.047 --> 46:40.884
She's all I've got,
but I'm not all she's got.

46:43.220 --> 46:45.055
And whatever happens, it's up to me

46:45.138 --> 46:48.308
to show her
you have to challenge injustice.

46:48.392 --> 46:49.601
Whatever it takes.

46:51.144 --> 46:52.479
You can't be taking this seriously.

46:52.563 --> 46:56.483
If they try to grab us again,
we are easier to pick off on our own.

46:57.109 --> 46:59.987
And New York is the last place
anybody expects us to be.

47:00.070 --> 47:01.655
Yes, because it's a stupid idea.

47:02.364 --> 47:06.660
Everything you're saying is true.
It's just-- What else have we got?

47:12.082 --> 47:13.917
He won't agree to it anyway.

47:32.477 --> 47:33.562
The police, please.

47:39.818 --> 47:40.819
Sorry.

47:41.737 --> 47:43.071
I was looking for you.

47:43.155 --> 47:44.156
We've been talking,

47:44.239 --> 47:46.867
and we've decided we should all go
to get the truth from Copeland.

47:46.950 --> 47:49.203
-Really?
-I know how it sounds,

47:49.953 --> 47:51.455
but it does make sense.

47:51.538 --> 47:53.665
-How?
-Because you need us.

47:55.918 --> 47:58.003
Do you really think
they've told you everything?

48:01.757 --> 48:04.218
-What about you?
-I'm an open book.

48:08.764 --> 48:10.307
Natalie would be dead now.

48:10.390 --> 48:11.600
You think?

48:12.726 --> 48:15.145
What do you mean?
She didn't know the safety was on.

48:15.229 --> 48:16.480
Or she did.

48:18.106 --> 48:21.443
Now I see why you're not a professor.

48:21.527 --> 48:23.529
It doesn't take much to fool you, does it?

48:23.612 --> 48:26.073
Maybe, but I'm perceptive in other ways.

48:28.242 --> 48:31.620
We're all a piece of this puzzle, Sean,
and you can't solve it without us.

48:32.287 --> 48:34.206
You've only got this far
because of Aadesh.

48:36.333 --> 48:37.960
At least think about it.

49:41.064 --> 49:42.482
Did you call the police?

49:47.487 --> 49:50.908
Don't lie to me, David, or I will know.

49:58.332 --> 50:01.543
Find a hat, coat, anything you can grab.

50:02.628 --> 50:04.588
We're going. Now.

50:10.010 --> 50:11.011
Come on.

50:23.815 --> 50:25.317
Get in.

50:28.070 --> 50:29.154
Wait, what's the rush?

50:50.425 --> 50:52.427
We need to switch vehicles fast.

50:57.933 --> 50:59.893
Get down. All of you. Now.
